{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DH61ft5YHbSoP1qbVtdbTL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a much clearer picture. Let me understand what the oracle needs:\n\n1. Pods running ES 8.11.1 image (not 7.17.9!)\n2. All 3 pods Ready\n3. ES cluster accessible via HTTPS at `es-http:9200` (HTTPS)\n4. `elastic-password` secret with password key\n\nThe precondition was supposed to:\n1. Create `openssl-toolbox` and `curl-test` pods\n2. Generate TLS certs and create `es-http-tls` secret\n3. Create `elastic-password` secret with password `elasticpass`\nBut the secrets are gone now. The stage_02 precondition probe found 4 running pods and skipped the apply section because of the `on_probe_fail: skip` logic—which means it never generated the TLS certs and password that the apply would have created. So stage_01 deployed a basic ES 7.17.9, then stage_02's probe succeeded on finding those pods and skipped the critical setup steps. So the precondition's probe succeeded because ES was already running from stage_01, which means the apply block that would've created the TLS and password secrets never executed. The precondition log confirms this - just the probe result, no apply or verify steps. This leaves me wondering whether stage_01 was supposed to create these secrets but failed to, or if the stage_02 precondition would've handled it if the probe hadn't short-circuited the whole thing.\n\nLet me look at how the bootstrap-initial-master-nodes case handles this in its test configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5402,"cache_read_input_tokens":36399,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5402},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":